<% content_for :page_title, "Application submitted" %>

<div class="govuk-panel govuk-panel--confirmation govuk-!-margin-bottom-6">
    <h1 class="govuk-panel__title">
        Your application has been submitted!
    </h1>
</div>

<h2 class="govuk-heading-m govuk-!-margin-bottom-2">What happens next?</h2>

<ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--number">

  <li>
    Your application will be allocated to an investment manager
  </li>

  <li>
    The investment manager will assess the project
  </li>

  <li>
    Your application will be considered in competition with other applications from your
    project's area/region
  </li>

  <li>
    You will know our decision within 8 weeks
  </li>

</ul>

<p class="govuk-body">
  <span class="govuk-!-font-weight-bold">
    If your project is in Inverclyde or North Lanarkshire we will prioritise your application.
  </span>
  This is because these local authority areas are currently under-represented in our funding.
</p>

<h2 class="govuk-heading-m govuk-!-margin-bottom-2">To receive funding your organisation must:</h2>

<ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">

  <li>
    have a UK bank account
  </li>

  <li>
    be able to legally receive funding. This means that your constitution allows you to receive funds
  </li>

</ul>